          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Deuterated polyethylene (C2D4) sample was used. Two",
                "targets were used: the initial 214 mu-g/cm2-thick",
                "film was replaced after 40 hours of beamtime with a",
                "thicker 350 mu-g/cm2 target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The SuperORRUBA array of segmented",
                "Si telescopes was used to detect tritons from the",
                " (d,t) reaction. The array comprised of seven E-dE",
                "telescopes from the ORRUBA array to identify the",
                "light ejectiles and four additional E detectors to",
                "monitor elastically-scattered deuterons for beam",
                "normalization. The respective thickness was 65 mu-m",
                "for dE and 1000 mu-m for E detectors. The telescopes",
                "were placed at a radial distance of 123 mm from the",
                "target. The large segmentation of the E detectors (64",
                "strips perpendicular to the beam direction) combined",
                "with the 8-fold segmentation (parallel to the beam",
                "direction) of the E detectors, resulted in an average",
                "resolution of 0.28 degrees in polar angle. The",
                "angular range covered by the telescopes and two of",
                "the E detectors was 35 - 50 degrees in the laboratory",
                "frame, while the two remaining E detectors were",
                "placed close to 90 degrees."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The radioactive 132Sn beam was produced via the",
                "proton-induced fission of 238U in a UCx target,",
                "extracted using the isotope separation online (ISOL)",
                "technique, and accelerated by the 25-MV ORNL Tandem",
                "electrostatic accelerator to 580 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The triton angular distributions were converted to",
                "absolute cross sections using the normalization",
                "determined from the elastic scattering of deuterons",
                "from the same target"
              ]
            }
          ],
